The traduction [and] mariage of the princesse
[16] p.
Richard Pynson, [London : 1500]
Imprint from STC. Printer's device (McKerrow 9b) with Pynson's name is on verso of leaf b4. The Bodleian Library copy, which duplicates none of the British Library text and lists names of the greeters and attendants, may belong to an earlier, separate publication. Both reflect the earliest plans for Catharine's reception, which underwent various changes before her arrival in October 1501--STC. Signatures: pi⁴ b⁴. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
